tp:treatment-sec.p:
Eggs laid free, spherical, with reticulated shell (
) and with processes in the shape of inverted goblets (
). Diameter without processes 69–78 µm, including them 74–86 µm. On circumference 23–27 processes were present ( 86–110 in hemisphere). Processes up to 5.9 µm high with basal diameter of 5.1–5.5 µm. Terminal disc, 3.8–5.5 µm in diameter, may appear smooth (
), but in some orientations it shows very small teeth (
). Egg shell with very regular, elegant, and homogeneous reticular design (
). Margins of meshes very thin and basal meshes slightly larger than others.

Description of the holotype :
Body length 312 μm, colorless; eyes present; cuticle with about 20 transversal undulations and some small, indistinct, and irregular in shape gibbosities (more evident in the caudal portion of the body) (
); other cuticular designs absent; gibbosities and tubercles on legs absent.

Mouth antero-ventral without peribuccal lamellae; peribuccal papulae not visible. Buccal armature simple consisting of two thin dorso-lateral and ventro-lateral ridges, large dorso-median round tooth and small and thin ventro-median triangular tooth (
). Buccal tube 38.3 μm long and 4.6 μm wide ( pt = 12.0 ) externally, with thick walls (
) and ventral lamina 22.0 μm long (
pt = 57.4 ). Stylet supports inserted on the buccal tube wall at 28.1 μm (
pt = 73.4 ).

Claws of 
Isohypsibiustype
, well developed (

). External claws with enlarged, smooth bases and with narrow lunules. Internal claws with short and thin bases (

) and with very small lunules. Other cuticular thickenings on legs absent. Main branches of claws with very thin accessory points (

); proximal portion of main and secondary branches of all claws swelled. Due to unfavourable orientation only anterior claws of hind legs were measured and were 
14.5
µm long (

pt = 
37.9
).

